.TH "calipso_opt_del" 9 "calipso_opt_del" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
calipso_opt_del \- Removes the CALIPSO option from an option header
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" calipso_opt_del
.BI "(struct ipv6_opt_hdr *hop "  ","
.BI "struct ipv6_opt_hdr **new "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hop" 12
the original header
.IP "new" 12
the new header
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates a new header based on \fIhop\fP without any CALIPSO option.  If \fIhop\fP
doesn't contain a CALIPSO option it returns -ENOENT.  If \fIhop\fP contains
no other non-padding options, it returns zero with \fInew\fP set to NULL.
Otherwise it returns zero, creates a new header without the CALIPSO
option (and removing as much padding as possible) and returns with
\fInew\fP set to that header.
